{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17515390","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17515390"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T13:31:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T13:31:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12450"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17583679","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17583679"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T07:24:24+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T07:24:24+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12450"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"12450","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/12450"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.28,0.26,0.26,0.07,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4958"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107363"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"4958","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/4958"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12450"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89849"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"41"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"78"},{"type":"tags","id":"1212"},{"type":"tags","id":"1840"},{"type":"tags","id":"2040"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"6099"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"8137"},{"type":"contributions","id":"8195"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13300"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34521"},{"type":"contributions","id":"39991"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41382"},{"type":"contributions","id":"48280"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107363","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/107363"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 30-year-old avid cyclist presents with a one month history of intermittent tingling in his right hand. He recently started training for a cycling marathon and this tingling has been interfering with his training. He has no significant medical history and does not take any medications. When asked to pinch a piece of paper with his right thumb and index finger at the web space, there is significant hyperflexion of the thumb at the interphalangeal joint.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following associated findings is most likely to be present?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Loss of sensation at the dorsal aspect of the 1st web space","Impaired flexion of the index finger at the interphalangeal joint","Loss of sensation at the dorsal medial half of the hand","Impaired extension of the 4th digit at the metacarpophalangeal joint","Impaired extension of the 5th digit at the proximal interphalangeal joint"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWith the observation of the compensatory use of flexion of the interphalangeal joint of his thumb, this patient has shown a positive Froment sign. The thumb hyperflexion is a response to the weakness/paralysis of the adductor pollicis, which is innervated by the ulnar nerve. The adductor pollicis is involved in thumb adduction and opposes thumb flexion via the flexor pollicis longus (innervated by the median nerve). The ulnar nerve is responsible for finger extension of the 4th and 5th digits at the proximal interphalangeal joints via lumbrical muscles, and entrapment can cause impaired extension. Therefore, the only abnormal sign that might be present in this patient is \u003Cstrong\u003Eimpaired extension of the 5th digit at the proximal interphalangeal joint\u003C/strong\u003E.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EChronic ulnar nerve compression is a common injury in cyclists due to the long-term pressure of the wrist against bike handlebars, causing ulnar nerve compression at the level of Guyon\u0027s canal in the wrist.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELoss of sensation at the dorsal aspect of the 1st web space\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. This region of sensory distribution is used to assess radial nerve sensation, and would not be affected in ulnar nerve compression based on this patient\u0027s presentation.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImpaired flexion of the index finger at the interphalangeal joint\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Flexion of the index finger at the interphalangeal joint is caused by the flexor digitorum superficialis or the lateral aspect of the flexor digitorum profundus, which are innervated by the median nerve. This would not be affected in ulnar nerve compression injuries.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELoss of sensation at the dorsal medial half of the hand\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. This region of the hand is innervated by the dorsal cutaneous branch of the ulnar nerve, which arises from the forearm proximal to Guyon\u0027s canal. As Guyon\u0027s canal compression is common in cyclists in the long-term, this region of sensation should be preserved. However, this type of presentation can arise in ulnar compression at the cubital tunnel.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImpaired extension of the 4th digit at the metacarpophalangeal joint\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect. Extension of the 4th digit at the metacarpophalangeal joint is mediated by the extensor digitorum muscle (innervated by the radial nerve). This muscle would not be affected in ulnar nerve compression injuries.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Ulnar nerve entrapment at Guyon\u0027s canal can cause a positive Froment sign, which is thumb hyperflexion due to an unopposed flexor pollicis longus and paralysis of the adductor pollicis.","Tinel\u0027s test can be used to assess both the median nerve and ulnar nerve for nerve entrapment, resulting in tingling/prickling sensation in the sensory distribution of the respective nerve."],"references":["Dy CJ, Mackinnon SE. Ulnar neuropathy: evaluation and management. Current Reviews in Musculoskeletal Medicine. 2016 Jun;9:178-84.","Sharrak S. Hand Nerve Compression Syndromes."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89849"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"12450"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19228"},{"type":"media","id":"19229"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19228","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19228"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/64143163-3b07-4eee-985c-3cfa045046db.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/64143163-3b07-4eee-985c-3cfa045046db.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1278,"height":1278}},{"type":"media","id":"19229","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19229"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/3a40c787-357b-4547-9772-198a1d4df52f.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/3a40c787-357b-4547-9772-198a1d4df52f.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1278,"height":1278}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"89849","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/89849"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-06-29T08:03:34+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-06-29T08:04:26+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"4958"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"107363"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https